<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Text_appearance_arm  Entity: Text_style  
   <express_ref linkend="text_appearance:arm:Text_appearance_arm.Text_style"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Text_appearance_arm.Text_style">
A <b>Text_style</b> is the identification of a collection of characteristics for the display of texts on a drawing sheet or on a screen.
<example>Font, character spacing are examples of such characteristics.</example>
<note>This entity is partially modelled in the ARM. However, in the MIM, all display characteristics for texts that exist in the resource part ISO 10303-46 are used. 
Detailed information about these characteristics can be obtained in ISO 10303-46.</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Text_appearance_arm  Entity: Text_style  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="text_appearance:arm:Text_appearance_arm.Text_style.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Text_appearance_arm.Text_style.name">
a string that specifies the name by which the text style is known.
<example>H1 is an example of name of text style, commonly used in HTML files.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Text_appearance_arm  Entity: Presentable_text_item  
   <express_ref linkend="text_appearance:arm:Text_appearance_arm.Presentable_text_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Text_appearance_arm.Presentable_text_item">
A <b>Presentable_text_item</b> is a type of <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b> that defines the geometric and display characteristics necessary for the presentation of a particular text.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Text_appearance_arm  Entity: Presentable_text_item  Attribute: literal 
   <express_ref linkend="text_appearance:arm:Text_appearance_arm.Presentable_text_item.literal"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Text_appearance_arm.Presentable_text_item.literal">
the string that may be presented on a drawing sheet or a screen.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Text_appearance_arm  Entity: Presentable_text_item  Attribute: style 
   <express_ref linkend="text_appearance:arm:Text_appearance_arm.Presentable_text_item.style"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Text_appearance_arm.Presentable_text_item.style">
the <b>Text_style</b> that is applied to the string.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Text_appearance_arm  Entity: Presentable_text_item  Attribute: placement 
   <express_ref linkend="text_appearance:arm:Text_appearance_arm.Presentable_text_item.placement"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Text_appearance_arm.Presentable_text_item.placement">
the <b>Axis_placement</b> that specifies the location and orientation of the text. 
<p>the origin of the axis placement identifies the position of the bottom-left corner of the text. 
the first axis of the axis placement identifies the direction of the text.</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Text_appearance_arm  Entity: Composite_presentable_text  
   <express_ref linkend="text_appearance:arm:Text_appearance_arm.Composite_presentable_text"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Text_appearance_arm.Composite_presentable_text">
A <b>Composite_presentable_text</b> is a type of <b>Detailed_geometric_model_element</b> that identifies a collection of presentable texts. 
<p>The structure of a <b>Composite_presentable_text</b> shall be acyclic.</p>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Text_appearance_arm  Entity: Composite_presentable_text  Attribute: collected_text 
   <express_ref linkend="text_appearance:arm:Text_appearance_arm.Composite_presentable_text.collected_text"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Text_appearance_arm.Composite_presentable_text.collected_text">
the set of 2 or more instances of <b>Presentable_text_item</b> or <b>Composite_presentable_text</b> that identifies the aggregated texts.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
